Many companies take advantage of anglers wanting to make a name for themselves on social media. I recognize that not all companies can pay their prostaff money, and I have worked with lots of companies that do not pay me but offer other tangible benefits. Each deal I analyze whether what I am receiving is worth the time and effort I put into the brand. I don’t forget that I am receiving a benefit (monetary, product or discount) in return for my services as a content creator. It is unfortunate that many do not understand the basics of quid pro quo. Know your worth!!! #knowyourworth #contentcreator #influencers #fishing #bassfishing

Believe in yourself! ⭐️ When I started tournament fishing, I was embarrassed at times for the things I didn’t know. But I decided that I would learn each time I fished on someone’s boat. I would take something away from that experience to learn and grow as an angler. I have learned so much in 3 years, and I know I have a lot still to go! When I’m not in tournaments, I am working on my fishing skills, learning things like driving a boat, backing a trailer, and reading maps and graphs. Don’t let yourself “feeling stupid” stand in the way of becoming greater 🙌

⬇️⬇️⬇️ 3 photos of my fishing journey 

If you asked me what I wanted when I started this fishing page in 2020, I would have said as a far-fetched dream to represent Yamamoto Baits. And, to my amazement, I achieved that goal in a few short years with the help and support of family, friends, and fans. My small Instagram fishing page showing off my catches at my family pond grew into tournament fishing, brand sponsorships, a lake record, and competing all over the US. And this is just the beginning…so much more to come! 

While fishing is now a business for me, it’s easy to lose sight of where I started and WHY I started. I feel so blessed to have had the opportunities and support from my sponsors. And some days making content is a “job” and not always fun, yet I don’t forget that there are lines of other people who would jump at the chance to represent the brands that I do. And that I represent these brands because I have faith in their products and I genuinely love fishing. 

I’m so thankful for the continued support and y’all sharing this journey with me. Excited for the 2024 tournament season!!! Onward and upward!
